b'(8/8) Our challenge to the #finance sector: The decisions some of you here make in boardrooms in the next few years will be critical as to whether we avoid human, ecological, and economic catastrophe. You have the power and the responsibility. #ClimateEmergency #ClimateStrike'

b'(7/8) Our key message about climate risk to the #finance sector: corporate focus is wrongly only on short-term profit generation, there is a fundamental misunderstanding of the risks being run, and inadequate regulatory oversight - akin to the 2008 crash.  #ClimateStrike'

b'(6/8) #Banks must rapidly align their business model with the goals of the Paris Agreement. The provision of all financial services to the fossil fuel industry must be phased out on a timetable consistent with meeting the Paris goals. #ClimateEmergency #ClimateStrike'

b'(5/8) If financial and other commercial actors will not voluntarily align with Paris Goals, regulators including Central Banks must use all of the tools at their disposal to change the current high-risk business as usual. #ClimateEmergency #ClimateStrike #finance'

b'(4/8) Regarding the newly launched Principles for Responsible Banking, @greenpeace believes that without concrete and ambitious targets, #banks risk turning this initiative into yet another greenwashing tool.\n#ClimateEmergency #ClimateStrike'

b'(3/8) Climate risk is not just transition risk.

The far more significant - and, if we continue as we do now, the more likely - risk comes from the consequences of failing to achieve a rapid and orderly transition to a low carbon #economy.
#ClimateEmergency #ClimateStrike'

b'(2/8) To #finance fossil fuel expansion is today\xe2\x80\x99s equivalent of betting the global economy - on subprime mortgage backed securities over a decade ago; fuelling a crisis, which is going to drag the whole global economy down with it.  \n\n#ClimateEmergency #ClimateStrike'
